            return marks;
        }
    }

Now your cell value factories can return appropriate values for each column. I fixed some of the ugly code here. I&#39;m not sure why you have a field called `studentNumber` which is a `String` (and not a numeric type of some kind), but I left it in case there is some good reason for it.

